<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 31 at 4:23PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Montgomery and Stanly Counties through 515 PM EDT...
At 422 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a thunderstorm with brief
heavy rainall and gusty wind over Midland, or 14 miles south of
Downtown Concord, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Brief wind gusts to 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Troy, Badin Lake, Plyler, Fairview In Union County,
Locust, Badin, Oakboro, Stanfield and Richfield.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
